
1. if statement syntax:

if (expression) {
 to be executed Statement (if that expression is true) ;
}
 <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var subject = 75;
            if (subject > 80) {
                document.write("<b>Got the pass mark!</b>");}
 </script>

2. if...else statement syntax:

if (expression) {
 to be executed Statement (if that expression is true);
} else
 to be executed Statement (if that expression is false);

     <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var subject = 75;
            if (subject > 80) {
                document.write("<b>Got the pass mark!</b>");
            } else {
                document.write("<b>Didn't get the pass mark</b>"); }
          </script>

3. if..else if...statement

if (expression 1) {
 to be executed Statement (if that expression 1 is true);
} else if (expression 2) 
 to be executed Statement (if that expression 2 is true);
} else {
 to be executed Statement (if that expression if none is true);}

     <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var subject = 75;
            if (subject > 80) {
                document.write("<b>Got the pass mark!</b>");
            } else if (subject == 75) {
                document.write("<b>The score was 75</b>");
            } else {
                document.write("<b>Didn't get the pass mark</b>");}
             </script>

Replace Them Below:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
    <html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>JavaScript if/else Application</title>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h3>JavaScript if/else Application</h3>
        <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            var subject = 75;
            if (subject > 80) {
                document.write("<b></Got the pass mark!b>");
            } else if (subject == 76) {
                document.write("<b>The score is 75!</b>");
            } else {
                document.write("<b>Didn't get pass mark!</b>");
            }
        </script>
    </body>
    </html>
